{{Infobox royalty | name = Afonso | title = Lord of [[Leiria]] | image = EU Member States' CoA Series- Portugal.svg | image_size = 120px | caption = | spouse = | issue = | house = [[Portuguese House of Burgundy]] | father = [[Afonso of Portugal, Lord of Portalegre]] | mother = [[Violante Manuel]] | birth_date = c. 1288 | birth_place = | death_date = c. 1300 | death_place = [[Lisbon]] | burial_place = | religion = [[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholicism]] |}}
'''Afonso of Portugal''' (c. 1288 &ndash; [[Lisbon]], c. 1300; {{IPA-pt|ɐˈfõsu}}; {{Lang-en|Alphonzo}} or ''Alphonse'') was a [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] noble, son of [[Afonso of Portugal, Lord of Portalegre]] and his wife [[Violante Manuel]]. He was granted the title of Lord of [[Leiria]]. Afonso of Portugal died in 1300 when he was about twelve years of age without having married and without leaving any offspring.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web |url = http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/PORTUGAL.htm#Affonsodied1312 |title= Foundation for Medieval Genealogy |accessdate= 11 November 2009 }}</ref>
