{{Infobox Christian leader | type = [[List of Patriarchs of the Church of the East|Catholicos-Patriarch of the Assyrian Church of the East]] | honorific-prefix = [[Mar]] | name = Shimun XVII Abraham | honorific-suffix = | title = His Holiness | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Assyrian Church of the East]] | province = | metropolis = | diocese = [[Patriarchal Diocese of Qodshanis]] | see = [[Apostolic See]] of [[Seleucia-Ctesiphon]] | enthroned = 1820 | ended = 1861 | predecessor = [[Mar Shimun XVI Yohannan]] | opposed = | successor = [[Shimun XVIII Rubil]] | ordination = | consecration = | rank = Catholicos-Patriarch | other_post = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Qodshanis]], [[Hakkari]] | death_date = 1861 | death_place = [[Qodshanis]], [[Hakkari]] | buried = | nationality = [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]] ([[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]]) | religion = [[Christian]], [[Assyrian Church of the East]] | residence = [[Qodshanis]], [[Hakkari]] | parents = | spouse = | children = | occupation = | alma_mater = | signature = | other = }} {{Eastern Christianity}} '''Mar Shimun XVII Abraham''' (also '''Simon XVII Abraham''' or '''Auraham''') was [[List of Patriarchs of the Church of the East|Patriarch]] of the [[Assyrian Church of the East]] from c. 1820 to 1861.{{sfn|Baum|Winkler|2003|p=127, 175}}
He led the church from [[Konak, Hakkari|Qodshanis]], (modern [[Konak, Hakkari]]) in southeastern [[Turkey]], and tried to maintain good relations with local [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] authorities. In 1843, he was faced with renewed hostilities from [[Kurds|Kurdish]] warlords, who attacked many Christian villages and killed 10,000 men, taking away women and children as captives, and forcing Patriarch to take refuge in [[Mosul]].{{sfn|Wilmshurst|2000|p=33, 212}} He is buried in the Church of Mar Shalita in Turkey.
